Django Project Git Ignore

--------------------------

1. Virtual Environment

--------------------------

Ignore the Python virtual environment folder

This is crucial as dependencies should be managed via requirements.txt

.venv
venv
env

--------------------------

2. Python Bytecode / Compiled files

--------------------------
__pycache__
*.pyc
*~$
pycache/

Coverage data

.coverage
.tox/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/

--------------------------

3. Operating System Files

--------------------------

.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

--------------------------

4. Database, Media, and Static Files

--------------------------

SQLite database files (usually named db.sqlite3)

DO NOT commit your local database file

*.sqlite3
*.db
.db-

Media and Static files uploaded/collected locally

You should explicitly manage production static/media file handling (e.g., S3/Azure)

/media/
/static_collected/

--------------------------

5. Environment Variables & Secrets

--------------------------

Critical: Never commit files containing secret keys, API keys, or database credentials.

Replace 'local_settings.py' with the actual filename if you use a different structure

(e.g., .env or settings.ini).

local_settings.py
.env
.env.local
.vscode/settings.json # VS Code specific local settings

--------------------------

6. Build/Frontend Artifacts (if building locally)

--------------------------

Ignore node modules and build artifacts that should not be part of the repository

node_modules/
dist/
build/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log